<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-06-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="203" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/541.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Enrique C.
                                    Creel</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chihuahua, Mexico</hi></placeName>,<lb/><date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-06-20"><hi rend="italic">June
                                        20, 1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I very highly appreciate the honor of your congratulations upon my return
                            from Central America. Your excellent work is well understood, and your
                            name is cherished by the people who are already enjoying the great
                            benefits of peace, order, and civilization.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Enrique C.
                            Creel.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>